column5: On our way up to Jacobs,we past this boat yard and said lets stop by on the way back.So we do just that and I was drooling and couldnt see me without this boat. It was a real bueaty.I have looked at these boats before. Heres some pics.            As for writing a cheque,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,Thankfully it was already sold.  The price tag,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,$45,000  Sweet looking machine tho.  Still look,n and wish,n.
$45,000  must be an error in price   :dunno:
I've seen those custom boats before Brian, they are awesome looking!!!
You didn't want it anyhow Brian.. they put the boarding ladder on the wrong side !

Thats a casting platform for Terry.    No error.Thats the price.I was shocked aswell.  The guy also sells the crestliner line.Guess what a 17ft fishpro goes for with a 115 on it?   Me thinks I,ll be taking a drive up to see Bernie soon.  Thats my best at photo crop/shop what ever.LOL
I seen those , can't believe the 45 k price tho. and welded to boot !  would be sweet for gbay !  TB
45K ouch...thats almost as much as my first house!
